<exercises xml:id="quick-practice-dtds" class="unnumbered">
<title>Quick practice</title>

<exercise><statement> <p> Is <m>x^*=0</m> an equilibrium point of
<m>x_{t+1} =
3x_t -1</m>?[quick-dtds1]</p></statement>
<solution>
<p> Since <m>3(0) - 1 \neq 0</m> (if I plug in zero and do
not get back zero), zero is not an equilibrium point.</p>
</solution>
</exercise>

<exercise><statement> <p> A population of size <m>p_t</m> increases by a
factor of
1.2, but only after 3 units are removed. Write the discrete-time
dynamical system describing the population dynamics.[quick-dtds2]</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p> To start we subtract <m>3</m> from <m>p_t</m>, that
resulting quantity is multiplied by the growth factor of <m>1.2</m>
resulting in the model <m>p_{t+1} = 1.2(p_t-3)</m>.</p>
</solution>
</exercise>
</exercises>
